Bushbaby Gaufrette - A Zendframework 2 module provides easy configuration and access to Gaufrette Filesystem

v.0.0.1 - unreleased


Configuration
1. configure one or more Gaufrette filesystems
2. configure your entity map

Usage
Simple Configuration
Get the Manager from the serviceLocator

    $manager = $sm->get('bsbFS');

Retrieve a Gaufrette FS from the manager (which acts as a service manager

    $fs = $manager->get('some-key');

some-key refers to what you configured in step 1

Entity Usage
When working with (entity) objects you can do the following

    $manager = $sm->get('bsbFS');
    $manager->persistPreviewImage($entity, 'content');
    $manager->persistPreviewImage($entity, 'path/to/file');

    if ($manager->hasPreviewImage($entity)) {
        $file = $manager->retrievePreviewImage($entity));
    }
    // $file instanceof Gaufrette\File
    // 'PreviewImage' is variable

Limitations
 - only the Local and SaveLocal adapters are implemented
 - can only persist/retrieve when an entity has an id

Planned
